text: VERY GOOD LIBRARY(if u are a rafflesian)

I enjoy this library for its aesthetics. Although it is new built in the 1990s, the interior architecture of the library is very old fashioned. It uses wooden tables and chairs. The carrels are comfortable too, making one enjoy studying alone. You can possibly not find any other libraries with carrels in Singapore.
Best place to study if you are a Rafflesian.
DAN BROWN IS HERE RUN DONT WALK HERE
really nice place to relax after a long school day. I really love the quietness of it and the type of furniture in the library
